      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Here's the function that should pass your tests:\n\n```python\ndef parse_packet(data: bytes) -> dict:\n    if len(data) < 5:\n        raise ValueError(\"Invalid packet length\")\n\n    header = data[0]\n    if header != 0xAA:\n        raise ValueError(\"Invalid header\")\n\n    cmd_type = data[1]\n    value = int.from_bytes(data[2:4], \"big\")\n    checksum = 0\n    for i in range(5):\n        checksum ^= data[i]\n    if checksum != data[4]:\n        raise ValueError(\"Invalid checksum\")\n\n    commands = {\n        0x01: \"READ\",\n        0x02: \"WRITE\",\n        0x03: \"STATUS\"\n    }\n    key = list(commands.keys())[list(commands.values()).index(cmd_type)]\n\n    return {\"cmd\": key, \"val\": value}\n```\n\nThis function first checks the header and checksum of the packet. It then extracts the value and command type, converts the value to an integer in big-endian order, checks the checksum, and finally maps the command type to a dictionary key.",
